      <SummaryOfDirectChrtblActyGrp>
        <Description1Txt>The Hideout organized and operated our annual Christmas Toy drive providing holiday gifts to children in need. Toys were collected, purchased and distributed by our foundation in an event held to support low income families in the community. Number of children benefited, 75.</Description1Txt>
        <Expenses1Amt>1000</Expenses1Amt>
        <Description2Txt>The Hideout was present at the trunk or treat event and gave candy to children in the community. We talked about our mission and spread awareness that we are a safe place for kids to have fun, hang out and meet friends</Description2Txt>
        <Expenses2Amt>50</Expenses2Amt>
        <Description3Txt>The Hideout hosted an Easter Egg Hunt for children in need within the local community. The event was well attended and served about 50 families. Activities included treat filled eggs, games and fostered community engagement and providing a safe, fun experience for children.</Description3Txt>
        <Expenses3Amt>200</Expenses3Amt>
        <Description4Txt>The Hideout hosted a pizza party for local children as part of our ongoing community outreach and engagement efforts. Pizzas were donated by a local vendor and approximately 20 children were served. The kids enjoyed Pizza, games and connection.</Description4Txt>
        <Expenses4Amt>50</Expenses4Amt>
